            "chars": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>LD.XI.R18</em></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Always think of your poor child Little D.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This note was likely added as a final temporal layer along with that describing the contents of the previous chapter (LD.XI.R16) as a retrospective summary. The language is a succinct summary of the letter&rsquo;s closing:&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&ldquo;That you will think of me (when you think of me at all), and of my true affection and devoted gratitude, always, without change, as of&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Your poor child</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Little Dorrit.&rdquo; (LD 457)&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"
